Keyword and oneliner of the instrument as it left the House
MEDICAID: Requires the Louisiana Department of Health to increase the reimbursement
rates for nonemergency medical transportation providers
Report adopts Senate amendments to:
1. Clarify that wheelchair-accessible nonemergency medical transportation (NEMT)
services receive an increased reimbursement rate as provided for in proposed law.
2. Require the La. Dept. of Health to promulgate rules to establish a NEMT rate
methodology for trips involving multiple passengers.
Report amends the bill to:
1. Make technical changes.
Digest of the bill as proposed by the Conference Committee
Proposed law requires the La. Dept. of Health (LDH) to establish a Medicaid reimbursement
rate for nonemergency medical transportation (NEMT) services, including wheelchair-
accessible NEMT, that reimburses, at a minimum, $14.50 per trip and $2.10 per mile.
Proposed law requires LDH to establish a NEMT rate methodology for multiple passenger
trips based on the number of passengers being transported.
Proposed law prohibits LDH from allowing an individual to be transported via NEMT to a
Medicaid covered service outside of the individual's parish of residence or contiguous
parishes unless the Medicaid managed care organization or LDH determines it to be medical
necessary.
Proposed law requires LDH, no later than 90 days from the effective date of proposed law,
to take all necessary actions to implement the provisions of proposed law.
Effective upon appropriation of funds by the legislature.
Effective upon signature of governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
(Adds R.S. 40:1257.2(C), (D)-(E))
